<!-- ##### STRUCT GtkSourceStyle ##### -->
<para>
The #GtkSourceStyle structure is used to describe text attributes
which are set when given style is used.
</para>

@mask: which fields of #GtkSourceStyle structure are taken
    into account. Note that mask unset for given attribute
    is not the same as the mask set and attribute being %FALSE.
    For instance, if GTK_SOURCE_STYLE_USE_BOLD is unset then
    whether text will be bold is determined using other styles
    applied to the text, while if GTK_SOURCE_STYLE_USE_BOLD
    is set and @bold is %FALSE then text will not be bold (given
    that the style has the top priority among the styles applied
    to given text).
@foreground: foreground color
@background: background color
@italic: italic
@bold: bold
@underline: underline
@strikethrough: strikethrough

